&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, service‑driven&lt;strong&gt; Lead Server &lt;/strong&gt;to join our exceptional dining team at Splendido. This role is perfect for hospitality professionals who excel in creating memorable dining experiences while maintaining the high standards of our luxury senior living community. Ideal candidates are confident multitaskers with strong problem‑solving abilities who thrive in fast‑paced environments, ensure smooth daily service operations, and take pride in delivering warm, polished, and attentive service to residents, family members, guests, and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is full-time. Weeknight,&amp;nbsp;weekend, and holiday availability required.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists restaurant management and oversees dining staff and operations to ensure that standards are being met and resident satisfaction is achieved.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assures accuracy of food orders and serves food and beverages in a safe, sanitary, and timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspects dining areas and workstations prior to and following each meal period to ensure that server and utility duties are completed, providing a clean, sanitary, and safe working environment according to Mather Standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completes related tasks and side work as assigned. Checks out servers and server assistants to ensure all end‑of‑shift duties are completed prior to staff leaving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently communicates resident and customer concerns to assistant management and/or management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists in maintaining and achieving departmental sanitation standards and goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains a friendly and welcoming demeanor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs server duties, including greeting tables, taking and placing accurate orders to the kitchen, suggesting food and beverage offerings, and closing checks in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies areas for improvement, proposes possible solutions, and participates in data collection and process changes as part of the Quality Assurance Process Improvement process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective interaction and communication skills; team player.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior service experience in a dining environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership abilities and the ability to deliver consistent, quality food and beverage service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years of prior serving experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;English language proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior supervisory experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The hourly base wage range provided is a good faith estimate of what Mather reasonably expects to pay for this position at the time of the posting. The actual hourly rate offered will be determined based on a variety of factors, including but not limited to relevant skills, certifications, years of experience, geographic location, and current market conditions. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Mather, we are committed to being inclusive, resilient, bold, and impactful—and that includes offering a total rewards experience designed to support our team members. This position may be eligible to participate in Mather’s benefit plan and the Team Member Appreciation Fund, if applicable. Eligibility for benefits is dependent on employment status and hours worked per pay period. Participation in the Team member Appreciation Fund is not guaranteed and may vary based on factors such as hire date and program eligibility requirements.

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Splendido at Rancho Vistoso, an award-winning luxury senior living wellness destination in Tucson, Arizona, exceptional experiences begin with exceptional leadership. As part of the Mather family of communities, Splendido is known for its commitment to whole-person wellness, resident-centered care, and operational excellence. Our on-site healthcare center, Sonora, offers residents peace of mind through a continuum of healthcare services should they ever need them—just one of the many comforts featured within our award-winning community. Sonora at Splendido provides Assisted Living, Memory Support, Medicare-certified Skilled Nursing Care, rehabilitation services, short-term respite stays, and hospice care in surroundings that are intimate, residential, and focused on wellness. Sonora at Splendido was recognized with the&amp;nbsp; AHCA/NCAL Bronze National Quality Award for its skilled nursing care, an honor recognizing dedication to quality care and continuous improvement.We are seeking an accomplished and licensed&amp;nbsp;Administrator to lead our healthcare operations while fostering a culture of wellness, safety, regulatory excellence, and resident-centered care. The ideal candidate will be a licensed Administrator in good standing with the Arizona Nursing Home Administrator Licensing Board, possess 5+ years of leadership experience in long-term care administration, hold CPR/AED certification, and demonstrate a strong working knowledge of state and federal regulations governing skilled nursing and assisted living communities. Candidates with a Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s degree in Health Services and experience within a Continuing Care Retirement Community (CCRC) or Life Plan Community are strongly preferred. This leader thrives in a wellness-driven environment, is passionate about creating meaningful moments for residents and families, and brings a proven ability to lead high-performing teams while driving quality, safety, compliance, and operational excellence. The successful candidate will be a visible, hands-on leader who embodies Mather&#39;s Wellness Model, Mission, Vision, Values, and Nextraordinary philosophy while helping advance Splendido&#39;s reputation as one of Arizona&#39;s premier senior living and healthcare destinations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full-time, 100% in-person salaried position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serves as risk, quality, and safety leader in the Life Centre to reduce and mitigate adverse events; enhances the quality of care and services to residents and customers. Provides leadership in the Life Centre in developing and maintaining a culture of safety at the community. Participates in Integrated Risk, Quality, and Safety meetings at local and HQ level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Leads planning and oversees implementation of therapeutic programs to maximize resident wellness.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Maintains census according to budget through marketing, resident and family satisfaction initiatives, and admissions programs&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Ensures that staffing is maintained via recruitment and retention strategies.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Leads licensing and survey processes and activities.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Ensures that all staff development, training, licensing and certification requirements are maintained.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Ensures that federal and state regulations are met.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Develops, follows, and enforces policies and practices to ensure consistency with current standards promulgated by local, state, and federal regulatory bodies.&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;An exciting full-time opportunity awaits at Splendido—an award-winning, wellness-focused luxury senior living community—for a nurse leader who brings together clinical expertise, operational insight, and a passion for improving resident outcomes. As Nurse Manager, MDS &amp;amp; Clinic Reimbursement, this role leads resident assessment and care planning processes, oversees MDS completion and reimbursement accuracy, and ensures alignment across clinical care, documentation, and regulatory requirements. Working closely with an interdisciplinary team, this leader evaluates resident conditions, develops comprehensive, person-centered care plans, supports ICD-10 coding accuracy, and guides nursing staff in delivering high-quality care. The position provides day-to-day clinical leadership, supports staffing and team development, and exercises independent judgment in decisions that impact compliance, quality outcomes, and operational performance. It also plays a critical role in survey readiness, quality assurance and performance improvement initiatives, and the use of clinical and operational data to strengthen outcomes and mitigate risk. This is an ideal opportunity for a nurse who thrives in a highly accountable environment requiring sound judgment, regulatory expertise, and the ability to &amp;nbsp; influence both clinical practice and organizational effectiveness. A current RN license and CPR/AED certification are required, along with strong clinical assessment, care planning, communication, and leadership skills. Experience with MDS, PPS reimbursement, ICD-10 coding, and nurse management is highly valued. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
